<p><img loading="lazy" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-17552" src="https://cisomag.eccouncil.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Bradley-J.-Schaufenbuel-150x150.jpg" alt="Bradley J. Schaufenbuel" width="150" height="150" srcset="https://cisomag.eccouncil.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Bradley-J.-Schaufenbuel-150x150.jpg 150w, https://cisomag.eccouncil.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Bradley-J.-Schaufenbuel-300x300.jpg 300w, https://cisomag.eccouncil.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Bradley-J.-Schaufenbuel-96x96.jpg 96w, https://cisomag.eccouncil.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Bradley-J.-Schaufenbuel.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" />Bradley J. Schaufenbuel is currently Vice President and Chief Information Security Officer at Paychex. He leads his infosec professionals to manage and monitor tasks focused on crisis management, security training and awareness, risk and compliance, identity management, managed file transfer, security engineering, security investigations, cyber intelligence, vulnerability management, and security architecture and application security. He has multiple years of experience working with the financial sector and has authored numerous books and research publications wide variety of topics related to information security and governance. Schaufenbuel also holds a license to practice law in Illinois and is a U.S. Supreme Court Bar member. He has served on several corporate and non-profit boards and is a regular speaker at industry conferences.</p>
